descript.abstract: The Traffic Signals feature class shows the location of traffic signals in the state of Florida for on system roadways as derived from event mapping Feature 322, characteristics MAINTAGC, SDESTRET, SIGNALID, SIGNALNC, SIGNALTY, SIGOPDTE, SIGSTRCT and TYPECABL from the FDOT Roadway Characteristics Inventory data.
descript.purpose: The FDOT Traffic Signal Locations feature class provides spatial information on locations of traffic signals in RCI. District Traffic Operations Office is responsible for collecting and maintaining this information for on-system roadways. Some characteristics have been created to assist districts with their specific traffic operations data collection needs.

edom.edomvd: Active Off the SHS - The Roadway ID or a segment of a Roadway ID that is not part of the State Highway System (SHS), which is maintained by others (counties or cities), yet for which FDOT collects certain data for reporting purposes.

edom.edomvd: EXCLUSIVE means excluded from standard mileage reports. These roads (including ramps, frontage roads, and similar configurations) are considered to be part of another road, not separate roads in their own right). The term is usually used in combination with Active-Exclusive (associated with an Active road on the State Highway System) or Active-Off-Exclusive (associated with an Active road that is not on the State Highway System).
